{{Notability|biography|date=September 2014}}
'''Mary French''' is an administrative law judge with the [[United States Social Security Administration]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cae-fpd.org/news/jul09.pdf |format=PDF |title=Federal Defender Newsletter |date=July 2009 |website=Cae-fpd.org |accessdate=2016-06-28}}</ref> For over twenty years, until 2009, she served as a [[federal public defender]] in the [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of California|Eastern District of California]]. She attended the [[University of California, Davis]], and graduated from the [[Cornell Law School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://members.calbar.ca.gov/fal/Member/Detail/126643|title=State Bar of CA :: Mary Melissa  French|first=The State Bar of|last=California|work=ca.gov|accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref>

Her clients and cases include [[Kenneth Fetterman]], one of the first prosecutions for online auction fraud, which ironically set the record for the most expensive painting to be "sold" online to date.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsreview.com/sacramento/Content?oid=oid%3A11546 |title=Prisoner of Love – Feature Story – Local Stories – April 4, 2002 – Sacramento News & Review |publisher=Newsreview.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-13}}</ref> and [[Adrian Lamo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.securityfocus.com/news/6888|title=Adrian Lamo charged with computer crimes|work=securityfocus.com|accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref>

