{{Infobox MP | name = Moulvi Agha Muhammad | honorific-suffix = |image = | office =Member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] | term_start =17 March 2008 | term_end = 31 May 2018 |constituency =[[Constituency NA-261|NA-261 (Pishin-cum-Ziarat)]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age| 1944 | 1 | 1 }} | birth_place = |nationality = Pakistani |party = [[Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam (F)]] }}
'''Moulvi Agha Muhammad''' ({{Lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|مولوی آغا محمد}}}}; born 1 January 1944) is a Pakistani politician who had been a member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]], from 2008 to May 2018.
==Early life== He was born on 1 January 1944.<ref name="pildat/dob">{{cite web|title=Detail Information|url=http://www.pildat.org/mna/rsDetail.asp?detid=261|accessdate=11 July 2017|date=21 April 2014|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140421144501/http://www.pildat.org/mna/rsDetail.asp?detid=261|archivedate=21 April 2014|df=}}</ref>
==Political career==
He was elected to the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] as a candidate of [[Muttahida Majlis-e-Amal]] (MMA) from [[Constituency NA-261|Constituency NA-261 (Pishin-cum-Ziarat)]] in [[Pakistani general election, 2008]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Lawmakers share wealth of detail with nation|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/622612|accessdate=9 April 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=20 April 2011|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170410051343/https://www.dawn.com/news/622612|archivedate=10 April 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=180 MNAs had declared no income tax in 2008|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/629170-180-mnas-had-declared-no-income-tax-in-2008|accessdate=9 April 2017|work=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170912161330/https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/629170-180-mnas-had-declared-no-income-tax-in-2008|archivedate=12 September 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Winning margin on 88 out of 272 National Assembly seats is 10,000 votes or less|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/618059-winning-margin-on-88-out-of-272-national-assembly-seats-is-10,000-votes-or-less|accessdate=9 April 2017|work=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203075743/https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/618059-winning-margin-on-88-out-of-272-national-assembly-seats-is-10,000-votes-or-less|archivedate=3 February 2017|df=}}</ref> He received 30,611 votes and defeated [[Muhammad Sarwar Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2008 election result|url=https://www.ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202008/Report,%20General%20Election%202008,%20Vol-II.pdf|publisher=ECP|accessdate=7 April 2018|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105060230/https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202008/Report,%20General%20Election%202008,%20Vol-II.pdf|archivedate=5 January 2018|df=}}</ref>
He was re-elected to the National Assembly as a candidate of [[Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam (F)]] (JUI-F) from Constituency NA-261 (Pishin-cum-Ziarat) in [[Pakistani general election, 2013]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Court allows MNA-elect to take oath|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1074760|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=18 December 2013|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123749/https://www.dawn.com/news/1074760|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=JUI-F names candidates for 14 NA seats|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/797739|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=25 March 2013|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123644/https://www.dawn.com/news/797739|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=JUI-F's Maulvi Agha Muhammad de-notified as MNA|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1132311|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=16 September 2014|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123605/https://www.dawn.com/news/1132311|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref> He received 48,712 votes and defeated Muhammad Essa Roshan, a candidate of [[Pashtunkhwa Milli Awami Party]] (PKMAP). In the same election, he ran for the seat of the National Assembly as an independent candidate from [[Constituency NA-263|Constituency NA-263 (Loralai-cum-Musakhel-cum-Barkhan)]] but was unsuccessful. He received 152 votes and lost the seat to [[Ameer Zaman]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2013 election result|url=https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202013%20report/Election%20Report%202013%20Volume-II.pdf|publisher=ECP|accessdate=7 April 2018|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180201140612/https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202013%20report/Election%20Report%202013%20Volume-II.pdf|archivedate=1 February 2018|df=}}</ref>
In 2014, he was disqualified as the member of National Assembly and re-election in the constituency was ordered.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tribunal disqualifies JUI-F MNA, orders re-polling on NA-261|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1130856|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=9 September 2014|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123751/https://www.dawn.com/news/1130856|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref> His National Assembly membership was later reinstated by The Supreme Court of Pakistan.<ref>{{cite news|title=SC temporarily reinstates membership of JUI-F MNA Maulvi Agha|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1132991|accessdate=25 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=19 September 2014|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326135503/https://www.dawn.com/news/1132991|archivedate=26 March 2017|df=}}</ref>
